goal.en:
On successful completion of this course, students will be able to:
1. use basic reading skills, such as skimming for main ideas, scanning for specific information, and guessing meaning from the context, to understand the main idea, and make inferences/predictions from the text;
2. understand the concept of collocation, word prefixes, roots and suffixes, and use them in writing;
3. understand the basic elements and structure of paragraph writing, and write according to the rules;
4. appreciate the joys of reading, and develop the interests of extensive reading.
